messages.subject: What's in your car?
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 5/9/02 3:15:31 PM Central Daylight Time, AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 5/9/02 3:15:31 PM Central Daylight Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< . The box died, we cleaned out the car to go camping... well you
know how THOSE things go (except those of you who are super-organized and
clean-freaks!)
>>
LOL!!! My dh just grimaces when he has to ride in my car (which is also the
only vehicle that holds all of us) because of the layer of stuff on the floor.
Mostly it's kid things, take along fun stuff they just ditch on the floor.
We always have some fun toys down there if someone is brave enough to dig
around.
I love the dictionary/atlas ideas.....we need a botanical dictionary this
week, all the questions have centered around botany.
Jared just learned today, that a cherry grows on a tree. It took a while but
I did find a picture of a cherry tree for him.
Ren
